md:
giải nghĩa từ "withdraw" sang tiếng việt; đưa ra nghĩa tiếng việt theo từ loại và đưa ra câu ví dụ, các từ liên quan và các từ trái nghĩa.

* Withdraw (verb) - rút lui, rút lại, rút khỏi
	+ Meaning: to take something back or away from a place or a situation
	+ Example: "She withdrew her application from the university."
	+ Related words: pull out, take out, remove
	+ Antonyms: deposit, add, insert

* Withdraw (verb) - rút tiền, rút vốn
	+ Meaning: to take money out of a bank or an account
	+ Example: "He withdrew $100 from the ATM."
	+ Related words: take out, pull out, cash out
	+ Antonyms: deposit, put in, add

* Withdraw (verb) - rút lui, lui lại
	+ Meaning: to move back or away from a place or a situation
	+ Example: "The army withdrew from the battlefield."
	+ Related words: pull back, fall back, retreat
	+ Antonyms: advance, move forward, push forward

* Withdraw (verb) - rút lại, hủy bỏ
	+ Meaning: to take back or cancel something that has been said or done
	+ Example: "He withdrew his statement and apologized for the mistake."
	+ Related words: take back, cancel, retract
	+ Antonyms: confirm, affirm, reiterate
